HEADWORD: Bois darc
<hw>Bois" d'arc"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[F., bow wood. So called
because used for bows by the Western Indians.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The Osage orange (<spn>Maclura aurantiaca</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>bois d'arc</qex> seems to be the characteristic growth of
the black prairies.</q> <rj><qau>U. S. Census (1880).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bois durci</ent>⟦br⟧
